In `ArrayExpressions.mo` there currently is a work around for nested indexing not working. Distilled down to its essentials:

```Modelica 
model NestedArrayExpressions
    Real z[3];
end NestedArrayExpressions;
model ArrayExpressions
    NestedArrayExpressions nested2[2];
equation
    nested2[1].z[:] = {4, 5, 6}; // We should also be able to index with `nested2[1].z`
    nested2[2].z[1] = 3;
    nested2[2].z[2] = 2;
    nested2[2].z[3] = 1;
end'ArrayExpressions
```

In general, there's a whole lot more of fancy indexing that we should support, but probably don't. Taken from [xogeny](http://book.xogeny.com/components/subsystems/comp_arrays/#arrays-of-components):

```Modelica 
record Vector3D
  Real x[3];
end Vector3D;

model ArrayExample
  Point p[2];
  Point q[2,3];
  Vector3D v[4];
equation
  p.x = {1, 2}; // p[1].x = 1, p[2].x = 2
  q[:,3].y = {4, 5}; // q[1,3].y = 4, q[2, 3].y = 5;
  q.x = [1, 2, 3; 4, 5, 6] // q[1,1].x = 1,
                           // q[1,2].x = 2,
                           // q[2,3].x = 6
  v.x[1] = {1, 2, 3, 4}; // v[1].x[1] = 1, v[2].x[1] = 2,
                         // v[3].x[1] = 3, v[4].x[1] = 4
  v[:].x[1] = {1, 2, 3, 4}; // v[1].x[1] = 1, v[2].x[1] = 2,
                            // v[3].x[1] = 3, v[4].x[1] = 4
  v[2:3].x[1] = {2, 3}; // v[2].x[1] = 2, v[3].x[1] = 3
  v[1].x = {1, 2, 3};   // v[1].x[1] = 1, v[1].x[2] = 2,
                        // v[1].x[3] = 3
end ArrayExample;
```
